OL,3,C'That's inhumane': New Zealand airport
OL,4,Cimposes three-minute hugging limit
OL,6,FThe airport's chief executive officer
OL,7,FDan De Bono told national broadcaster
OL,8,FRadio New Zealand (RNZ) that people
OL,9,Fwere taking too long in the drop-off
OL,10,Fzone, saying there was "no space left
OL,11,Ffor others".
OL,13,F"We're trying to have fun with it. It
OL,14,Fis an airport and those drop-off
OL,15,Flocations are common locations for
OL,16,Ffarewells," he said.
OL,18,F"It's about enabling others to have
OL,19,Fhugs."
